@primozroglicshop
Ex skijumper from Slovenia, now a pro cyclist riding for Team Jumbo - Visma🚴🏻

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Primoz Roglic on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'PEAK'.

node.text:
As the Olympic games came to an end, I would like to congratulate to all athletes & staff and to our families who encourage and support us.

I would like to express gratitude to the organizers @tokyo2020 that made it all possible in this weird time for the world.
Thank you 🇯🇵 for the hospitality, to offer us a playground, where we had a chance to turn our dreams into reality.
 
I am extremely proud to represent my country 🇸🇮 and
grateful for all the fans that supported us from all over the world.

The moment I experienced as an Olympic champion on the podium, listening to our national anthem, was one the best in my career. 🥇
@sloveniaolympicteam
#olympics
#olympicchampion
📸CorVosPhoto

node.text:
Not the way I expected or wanted  to finish @letourdefrance in my beloved Tignes. I was in too much pain, so I had to quit.
But once again - the fans that awaited for me in front of the hotel, showed why is worth fighthing for💪
hvala navijači 🙌
 Thanks to @tourdetietema for catching the moment.
We will be back💪🙌
#tdf2021 #teamjumbovisma #samenwinnen #cyclinglife
